{"format": "tiptap/v1", "updatedAt": "2026-06-22T17:53:08.048Z", "doc": {"type": "doc", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "A "}, {"type": "text", "text": "transformer block", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}]}, {"type": "text", "text": " repeats two sublayers: multi-head self-attention and a position-wise feed-forward network (FFN). The FFN applies the same MLP to each token independently, adding non-linear capacity. Stacking many blocks\u2014attention for mixing, FFN for processing\u2014is what turns raw embeddings into the representations agent models use for tool selection and language."}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 2}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "What it is"}]}, {"type": "image", "attrs": {"src": "data:image/svg+xml;base64,", "alt": "Transformer block: attention plus FFN sublayers with residual connections and FFN expansion diagram"}}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 3}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Full transformer block"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "One block (pre-norm variant common in LLMs):"}]}, {"type": "codeBlock", "attrs": {"language": "text"}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "x = x + SelfAttn(LayerNorm(x))\nx = x + FFN(LayerNorm(x))"}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 3}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Feed-forward sublayer"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "For each token vector "}, {"type": "inlineMath", "attrs": {"latex": "x \\in \\mathbb{R}^{d_{\\text{model}}}"}}, {"type": "text", "text": ":"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "inlineMath", "attrs": {"latex": "\\text{FFN}(x) = W_2 \\, \\sigma(W_1 x + b_1) + b_2"}}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Typically "}, {"type": "inlineMath", "attrs": {"latex": "W_1"}}, {"type": "text", "text": " expands to "}, {"type": "inlineMath", "attrs": {"latex": "d_{\\text{ff}} \\approx 4 \\, d_{\\text{model}}"}}, {"type": "text", "text": ", "}, {"type": "inlineMath", "attrs": {"latex": "\\sigma"}}, {"type": "text", "text": " is GELU or SwiGLU, then "}, {"type": "inlineMath", "attrs": {"latex": "W_2"}}, {"type": "text", "text": " projects back. SwiGLU uses gated linear units: "}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "inlineMath", "attrs": {"latex": "\\text{SwiGLU}(x) = (xW_1) \\odot \\sigma(xW_3)"}}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 2}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Why it matters"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Attention mixes information between tokens; FFN "}, {"type": "text", "text": "transforms each token's vector locally", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}]}, {"type": "text", "text": ". Without FFN depth, the model would mostly re-weight existing features. Agent behaviors\u2014mapping natural language to strict JSON schemas, applying policy rules\u2014depend on deep FFN stacks after attention has gathered context."}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 2}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Benefits"}]}, {"type": "bulletList", "content": [{"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Large MLP inner dimension increases model capacity and parameter count efficiently"}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Per-token parallelism\u2014FFN is "}, {"type": "inlineMath", "attrs": {"latex": "O(n \\cdot d_{\\text{model}} \\cdot d_{\\text{ff}})"}}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Residual connections let gradients flow through deep stacks (dozens of blocks)"}]}]}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 2}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Trade-offs"}]}, {"type": "bulletList", "content": [{"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "FFN layers hold most parameters in many LLMs (especially with SwiGLU)"}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "MoE replaces dense FFN with routed experts\u2014better scale but complex inference"}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Depth increases latency linearly with layer count during decode"}]}]}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 2}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Performance and scalability"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Inference optimizes FFN matmuls heavily (quantization, fusion). For agents, time-to-first-token scales with prompt length and layers; tokens-per-second during tool argument streaming scales with FFN and attention at each decode step."}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 2}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Mental model"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Attention is a meeting where tokens share notes; FFN is each token thinking privately about what to do with those notes before the next meeting."}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 2}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Key takeaways"}]}, {"type": "bulletList", "content": [{"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Transformer block = attention + FFN, each with residual + norm"}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "FFN is position-wise MLP, typically 4\u00d7 expansion"}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Depth (number of blocks) drives model capability and inference cost"}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Agent LLM quality scales with stack depth and width, not attention alone"}]}]}]}]}}